==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Punk
<hw>Punk</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf.
<er>Spunk</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Wood so decayed as to be dry,
crumbly, and useful for tinder; touchwood.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A fungus (<spn>Polyporus fomentarius</spn>, etc.)
sometimes dried for tinder; agaric.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>An artificial tinder. See <er>Amadou</er>, and
<er>Spunk</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>A prostitute; a strumpet.</def>
<mark>[Obsoles.]</mark> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Punka</ent>⟦br⟧
\'d8
